{"word":"φρόνησις","slug":"φρόνησις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φρόνησις</b></el> <el>(φρόνησις, εως,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φρονέω'><el>φρονέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a minding</i> to do so and so, <i>purpose, intention</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>arrogance</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>thoughtfulness, prudence</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}